Package ca.mcgill.ecse211.project

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ColorCalibrator
    This class is used to check the color of a ring under a light sensor
    Display
    This class is used to display the content of the odometer variables (x, y, Theta)
    GameUtil
    Game utility class with handy functionalities can be used in the game
    GameUtil.PathFinder
    Class that find the shortest path from one point to another with constraints inside one area
    Main
    This class implements the main starting point for our final project
    Navigation
    The Navigator class extends the functionality of the Navigation class.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ColorCalibrator.Color
    This enumeration contains the possible colors of the ring under a light sensor
    Game
    This singleton contains all the methods and structures necessary to start competing in a game
    Game.Status
    This enumeration stores the possible states that our robot can be in during a competition
    GameParameters
    This singleton contains all the game parameters needed for the competition
    GameParameters.AreaType
    This enumeration contains the possible types of areas that our robot is currently located in
    GameParameters.DemoType
    This enumeration contains the type of demo that our robot is currently going to be performing in
    WiFi
    This class implements the ability to receive game parameters over WiFi
